recalls.Component: BACK OVER PREVENTION: SENSING SYSTEM: CAMERA
recalls.Summary:
BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2019-2021 X3 sDrive30i, X3 xDrive30i, X3 M40i, X3M, X4 xDrive30i, X4 M40i, M550i, X4M, X5 sDrive40i, X5 xDrive40i, X5 xDrive50i, X5M, X5 M50i, X7 xDrive40i, X7 xDrive50i, X7 M50i, Alpina XB7, 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, M340i xDrive, and 8 Series Coupe, Convertible and Grand Coupe, 840i, 840i xDrive, M850i xDrive, M8, 2020-2021 530e, 530e xDrive, 330e, 330e xDrive, 745Le, 745Le xDrive, X5 xDrive45e, X3 xDrive30e, X6 sDrive40i, X6 xDrive40i, X6 xDrive50i, X6 M50i, X6M, 530i, 530i xDrive, 540i, 540i xDrive, M550i xDrive, M5, 740i, 740Li, 740Li xDrive, M760i Drive, M760Li xDrive, 750Li xDrive Alpina, Alpina B7 xDrive, and 2021 4 Series Coupe 430i, 430i xDrive, M440i xDrive vehicles.

When shifting into Reverse, a small portion of the rearview image may be obscured, or the screen may not illuminate.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 111, "Rear Visibility."
recalls.Consequence: If the driver relies on only the rearview camera image, the missing or reduced rearview image view can increase the risk of a crash or injury.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the rearview camera software and update it if necessary, free of charge.  The recall began April 16, 2021.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Component: BACK OVER PREVENTION: SENSING SYSTEM: CAMERA
recalls.Summary:
BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2018 540d, 2018-2020 530i, 530i xDrive, 540i, 540i xDrive, M550i xDrive, M5, 530e, 530e xDrive, X3 sDrive, X3 xDrive, X3 M40i, X3 M, and 2019-2020 X4 xDrive, X4 M40i, X4 M, X7 xDrive, X7 M50i, 740Li, 740Li xDrive, 750Li, 750Li xDrive, 8 Series Convertible and Coupe 840i, 840i xDrive, M850i xDrive, X5 sDrive, X5 xDrive, X5 M50i, X6 xDrive, X6 M50i, 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, M340i xDrive, Z4 sDrive, Z4 M40i, 740Le xDrive and 745Le xDrive, 2018-2019 640i xDrive Gran Turismo and Rolls-Royce Phantom, 2019 M850i xDrive Gran Coupe and Rolls-Royce Cullinan and 2020 Toyota Supra vehicles.  

The back-up camera and display settings can be adjusted such that the rear view image is no longer visible and the system will retain that setting the next time the vehicle is placed in reverse.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 111, "Rearview Mirrors."
recalls.Consequence: The lack of an image in the back-up camera display increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will update the back-up camera software, free of charge.  The recall began November 8, 2019.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417 or Rolls-Royce at 1-877-877-3735.  Toyota owners may contact Toyota customer service at 1-888-270-9371.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2019 Z4 sDrive30i, 2019-2020 330i xDrive, M340i and M340i xDrive, 2020 X3M and X4M, and Toyota Supra vehicles.  In certain driving conditions, such as high temperatures and rough road surfaces, a steering gear tie rod may become damaged, possibly resulting in a fractured tie rod.
recalls.Consequence: A damaged or fractured tie rod may affect vehicle handling and control, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW and Toyota will notify owners, and dealers will replace the steering gear tie rods, free of charge.  The recall began August 14, 2020.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417 or Toyota customer service at 1-888-270-9371.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2019-2021 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i xDrive, 2020-2021 X3 sDrive30i, X3 xDrive30i, X3 M40i, X3M, 2021 X3 xDrive30e, X4 xDrive30i, and X4M vehicles.  The seat frame may not have been welded properly to the seat rails.
recalls.Consequence: An improperly welded seat frame may not properly restrain the occupant during a crash, increasing the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the seat frame and back rest, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed May 22, 2023. Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2019-2022 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, 2022 430i Coupe, 2021-2022 430i, M440i Convertible, and 2020-2022 228i xDrive Gran Coupe vehicles.  The receiver audio module control unit software may fail to properly generate audible seat belt warnings to the driver to fasten their seat belt.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: An audible chime that does not properly alert the driver to fasten their seat belt increases the risk of injury in a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the receiver audio module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed October 12, 2023.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

issues.title: B58 Engine Oil Pump Drive Chain Failure
issues.description: The oil pump drive chain can stretch or break, leading to complete loss of oil pressure and potential catastrophic engine failure. This is a known issue with the B58 engine used in the M340i.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement. BMW has issued updated oil pump chain components for affected vehicles.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, monitor oil pressure, address any unusual engine noises immediately

issues.title: ZF 8HP Transmission Rough Shifting
issues.description: The ZF 8-speed automatic transmission experiences harsh shifting, delayed engagement, or slipping between gears, particularly when cold or under heavy acceleration.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update, fluid change, or internal component replacement depending on severity
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving when transmission is cold

issues.title: High Pressure Fuel Pump (HPFP) Failure
issues.description: The high pressure fuel pump can fail prematurely, causing fuel starvation, reduced power, and potential engine damage. Common issue across BMW turbocharged engines.
issues.fix_description: Replace high pressure fuel pump and related components, update engine software
issues.prevention: Use high quality fuel, regular fuel system cleaning, avoid running on low fuel

issues.title: Carbon Buildup on Intake Valves
issues.description: Direct injection engines suffer from carbon buildup on intake valves due to lack of fuel washing over the valves, leading to reduced performance and rough idle.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves, decarbonization service
issues.prevention: Regular use of top-tier gasoline, occasional high RPM driving, carbon cleaning service every 30-40k miles

issues.title: iDrive Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: The iDrive 7.0 system can freeze, become unresponsive, or reboot randomly, affecting navigation, climate control, and vehicle settings.
issues.fix_description: Software update, system reset, or head unit replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid extreme temperatures, proper system shutdown

issues.title: Coolant Loss and Thermostat Issues
issues.description: Coolant leaks from various points including the thermostat housing, water pump, and radiator connections. Can lead to overheating if not addressed.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty thermostat housing, water pump, or radiator components as needed
issues.prevention: Regular coolant system inspection, maintain proper coolant levels, use BMW approved coolant

issues.title: Brake Pad and Rotor Premature Wear
issues.description: M Sport brake components wear faster than expected, particularly the front brake pads and rotors, requiring frequent replacement.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads and rotors, upgrade to higher performance compounds if desired
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive braking, regular brake inspection, proper bedding-in procedure

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: The turbocharger wastegate can develop a rattle or chattering noise, particularly during startup or low RPM operation.
issues.fix_description: Turbocharger repair or replacement, wastegate actuator replacement
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper grade, allow engine to warm up properly, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Adaptive LED Headlight Malfunction
issues.description: Adaptive LED headlights can malfunction, losing auto-leveling function or individual LED elements failing, affecting nighttime visibility.
issues.fix_description: Headlight module replacement or LED driver repair
issues.prevention: Avoid aftermarket LED bulbs, protect from moisture, regular electrical system checks

issues.title: Differential Mount Failure
issues.description: The rear differential mount can fail prematurely, causing vibrations, clunking noises, and potential driveline damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace differential mount with updated part number
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, regular drivetrain inspection, gentle driving during break-in period

editorial.tagline: The sweet spot between luxury and lunacy
editorial.hero_blurb: The M340i represents BMW's mastery of the middle ground - delivering genuine M-car thrills without the compromises. This is the thinking enthusiast's choice, blending everyday usability with weekend warrior capability in one perfectly balanced package.
editorial.essence: BMW's M340i strikes the perfect balance between performance and practicality that the brand has been chasing for decades. It's fast enough to embarrass proper sports cars yet refined enough for daily duties, embodying the original spirit of the Ultimate Driving Machine.
editorial.heritage: Built on BMW's acclaimed G20 3 Series platform, the M340i continues the legacy of the legendary E46 M3 - offering serious performance in a practical sedan body. It bridges the gap between the standard 3 Series and the full-fat M3, creating a new sweet spot in BMW's lineup.
editorial.design_philosophy: The designers aimed to create a stealth performer - aggressive enough to hint at its capabilities but subtle enough to slip under the radar. Clean lines, functional aero elements, and purposeful stance communicate intent without screaming for attention.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct race car derivative, the M340i benefits from BMW's extensive M division knowledge and track-proven technologies filtered down from the M3/M4 program.
editorial.engine_character: The B58 twin-turbo inline-six is a masterpiece of modern engineering - smooth as silk yet explosive when provoked. It builds power linearly with minimal turbo lag, delivering that classic BMW straight-six character enhanced by forced induction.
editorial.transmission_feel: The ZF 8-speed automatic is telepathic in its responses, delivering crisp shifts in auto mode and satisfying manual control via paddles. Launch control transforms it into a proper catapult when needed.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The chassis strikes an incredible balance between comfort and control, soaking up road imperfections while remaining composed during spirited driving. The adaptive dampers transform character at the touch of a button.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and well-weighted with just enough feedback to communicate road surface without being harsh. The variable ratio system provides easy parking maneuvers and razor-sharp turn-in when pushed.
editorial.brake_confidence: The M Sport brakes inspire complete confidence with strong initial bite, excellent pedal feel, and impressive fade resistance. They're perfectly matched to the car's performance capabilities.
editorial.sound_signature: The B58 produces a cultured growl that builds to a satisfying roar under full acceleration. It's sophisticated rather than shouty - unmistakably BMW with a hint of menace.
editorial.ideal_owner: The M340i is perfect for the accomplished professional who appreciates fine engineering and wants genuine performance without sacrificing daily usability or comfort.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Track-focused drivers seeking maximum performance, badge snobs who need the full M treatment, or buyers prioritizing fuel economy and low running costs above all else.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service history, as the B58 engine rewards proper care. The M340i represents exceptional value in the performance sedan segment, offering 90% of M3 thrills at a fraction of the running costs.

expertReviews.title: 2025 BMW M340i (G20) Review || Heart-Stopping M3 ...
pros: B58 3.0L turbo inline-6 engine with 386 hp and 398 lb-ft torque
Excellent fuel economy - over 35 mpg despite nearly 400 horsepower
Exceptional exhaust sound - natural inline-6 note
Quick acceleration - 0-60 in 4.4 seconds, only 1 second slower than M3
Excellent 8-speed automatic transmission with dual-clutch-like responses
M Sport suspension, brakes, and variable ratio steering
Good visibility and comfortable seating position
Retains BMW sports sedan driving character despite modern tech
Standard 19-inch wheels with M Sport red brake calipers
Arctic Race Blue metallic paint option is gorgeous
cons: No spare tire - only tire repair kit
Key fob design feels dated compared to other BMW models
Some digitization reduces analog feel compared to older 3 Series
Price approaches $67,000 with options
Exhaust finishers aren't true dual tips
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 BMW M340i successfully bridges the gap between comfort and performance, delivering near-M3 acceleration with excellent fuel economy. The B58 engine with mild-hybrid assistance provides 386 hp and an intoxicating sound, while maintaining the core BMW sports sedan driving experience. Despite some modern compromises, it retains enough analog feel to satisfy driving purists while offering practical daily usability.

expertReviews.title: 2025 BMW M340i Review
pros: 382 horsepower 3.0L turbocharged inline-6
Premium M Sport seats with leg extension support
Spacious rear seating with good headroom and legroom
Wireless CarPlay and Android Auto with 14.9-inch infotainment
Adaptive suspension and variable sport steering
Functional aerodynamic elements without being over the top
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 M340i is described as the 'Goldilocks' of BMW's 3 Series lineup - not as visceral as the M3 but not as tame as the 330i. It maintains BMW's driving characteristics while elevating luxury, making it an ideal sports sedan for genuine daily driving with 382hp, 0-60 in 4.1 seconds, and premium interior features.

expertReviews.title: 2025 BMW M340i Review: Better Than an M3 for Daily Driving?
pros: Excellent fuel economy (31 mpg average, up to 40 mpg highway)
Strong performance (389 hp, feels 90-95% of M3 capability)
Great daily driver comfort and practicality
Bulletproof B58 engine reliability
Significant savings vs M3 ($30-40k less)
New B58 TU2 engine with port and direct injection
Lightweight at 3750 lbs vs competitors at 4200-4300 lbs
cons: Seats not comfortable for long drives and lack side bolstering
Harman Kardon sound system underwhelming for price point
Gets tossed around in canyons due to inadequate seat support
expertReviews.verdict: The M340i strikes an excellent balance as a one-car solution, delivering 90-95% of M3 performance while being much more practical and affordable. The updated B58 TU2 engine adds power and reliability improvements. Despite minor comfort issues with seats and audio system, it's an outstanding sports sedan for daily driving and spirited canyon runs, saving $30-40k over an M3 while maintaining bulletproof reliability.

expertReviews.title: 2023 BMW M340i LCI Review: Better Than the M3??
pros: Exceptional performance from B58 3.0L inline-6 turbo engine
Advanced OS8 infotainment system with responsive touchscreen and iDrive controller
Excellent build quality with premium materials throughout
All-wheel drive system with rear-biased torque distribution and limited slip differential
Effective braking system with M Sport package upgrades
Fuel efficient despite high performance
Advanced safety technology and driver assistance features
cons: High price around 105,000-120,000 on road
Keyless entry appears to be missing or non-functional
Climate controls moved to touchscreen instead of physical buttons
Gear selector replaced with less functional knob design
No privacy glass on rear windows
Limited rear seat toe room compared to SUVs
expertReviews.verdict: The 2023 BMW M340i LCI delivers exceptional performance that rivals the M3, with the legendary B58 engine providing devastating acceleration and an addictive sound. The updated OS8 system and premium interior materials showcase BMW's commitment to luxury, though some ergonomic changes like the touchscreen climate controls are questionable. Despite the high price, the combination of performance, technology, and daily usability makes this a compelling alternative to the full M3.

expertReviews.title: Why The M340i Is The Best Daily Performance Car | Driven+
pros: Perfect balance of everyday usability and performance
Excellent B58 3.0L straight-six engine with 369hp stock
Responds very well to ECU tuning (450hp with stage 1)
All-wheel drive system with rear-bias for better handling
More comfortable and practical than M3
Great interior with iDrive 7 system
Largest boot space in class at 480L
Excellent ZF 8-speed automatic transmission
Better value than competitors like Audi S4/S5 and Mercedes C43
cons: Weighs 1.8 tons which is quite heavy
Steering lacks feedback compared to M3
Cannot be switched to rear-wheel drive only mode
No manual gearbox option available
Not as track-focused as the M3
expertReviews.verdict: The M340i is described as the perfect daily performance car that excels at being an all-rounder. It offers the right balance of comfort, practicality, and performance without the harshness of the M3. With excellent tuning potential and superior everyday usability, it's considered better value than its German rivals and the ideal choice for those wanting one car to do everything.
